  "enabling_type": "background",
  "certainty": 0.9,
  "source_text_quote": "Under the British policy of salutary neglect, Britain traded with the colonies but otherwise mostly left them alone over the first 150 years of the colonies\u2019 existence. The colonists became accustomed to running their own affairs, and they liked it."
}

{
